text: Eunidia ziczac is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939. It is known from South Africa, Malawi, and Zimbabwe.BioLib.cz - Eunidia ziczac. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 4.5 mm long and 1 mm wide, and its type locality is "Natal". It is named for the zig-zag pattern on its elytron. ==References== Category:Eunidiini Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Eunidia ziczac
